snippet.textDisplay: So far everyone commenting about the lights is correct. They are for driving with NVG's (Night Vision Goggles). As for the Panel with the phone connectors and 2 round ports. That is where the Generator would connect in. The generator would connect to one of the round ports to provide 120V to the inside. The phone connector is for the old style phones. 2 wire system. If i remember correctly the Generators were 3 Phase and the electronics inside the back would step it down from 3 Phase to 120V. Hope this info helps.
snippet.textOriginal: So far everyone commenting about the lights is correct. They are for driving with NVG's (Night Vision Goggles). As for the Panel with the phone connectors and 2 round ports. That is where the Generator would connect in. The generator would connect to one of the round ports to provide 120V to the inside. The phone connector is for the old style phones. 2 wire system. If i remember correctly the Generators were 3 Phase and the electronics inside the back would step it down from 3 Phase to 120V. Hope this info helps.

snippet.textDisplay:
O-Ring- (Turret- for guns or system)
M-16 mounts, 5.56mm American Rifle system (AR-15 long butt stock)
Pouch under turret- is for catching brass as you pour American lead.
Batteries- just batteries, but I think these have to be 24v set-up.
Bars over gauges- for gunner to put feet on without breaking.
Box in back is Kevlar lined.
The passenger side wire- where the comms antenna goes
All fluids can be checked behind the driver seat.
Look for the M1079 truck TM-10
Yes you can upgrade the lights, however I would just splice them in.
Military Grade- Lowest Bidder
